INSERT INTO `BCCEventData` VALUES ('Connecting Waves: A Saltwater Woman Living on Desert Country Exhibition','Elisa Jane Carmichael is a Ngughi woman from Quandamooka country living on Arrernte country in Mparntwe (Alice Springs). As the Gilimbaa Artist in Residence, she is recording and documenting her personal and creative journey as a saltwaterwoman living in desert country, weaving and painting her connection to the sand and sea and home country through woven objects and canvases.  Gallery is open from 10am-5pm Wednesday to Friday and 9am-3pm on Saturday.  This exhibition is a part of the Quandamooka Festival 2017 and Brisbane City Council’s Black History Month.','Onespace Gallery, 13a Gladstone Road, Highgate Hill','2017-07-04 14:00:00','2017-08-05 14:00:00','Brisbane City Council','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0),('Queensland Music Festival','Katie Noonan (Artistic Director) will bring together the best of local, national and international musicians in the Queensland Music Festival in July.  Audiences are invited to get personally involved by joining the Festival’s signature event, You’re the Voice. This free event will see the South Bank Piazza filled with Queensland choirs as they sing for change on Saturday 29 July. Get involved and join the sea of voices at Queensland Music Festival.','Various locations across Brisbane','2017-07-06 14:00:00','2017-07-30 14:00:00','Brisbane City Council','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0),('GovHack 2017','GovHack 2017 is an annual 46 hour hackathon where teams create a project page, proof of concept and a video that tells the story of how government open data can be reused. The competition is held across Australia and New Zealand on 28-30 July 2017. GovHack 2017 is a volunteer run not-for-profit community initiative and is a free event to attend and participate.&nbsp;  Data Mentors will be in attendance to share their knowledge of open government data and to provide insight that could help incubate ideas to pursue during the competition.  GovHack 2017 is proudly sponsored by Brisbane City Council.','Various locations across Brisbane','2017-07-27 14:00:00','2017-07-30 14:00:00','Brisbane City Council','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0),('Jan Powers Farmers Markets','Every Saturday morning, the walkway at the front of Brisbane Powerhouse fills with market stalls selling a variety of fresh products. Pick up your morning coffee and enjoy the food, fresh produce, meat, seafood, cakes bread and more on offer. You can also bring your dog along to this pooch friendly market.','Brisbane Powerhouse, New Farm','2017-07-28 20:00:00','2017-07-29 02:00:00','Brisbane City Council','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0),('Back to basics','Bookings essential. Learn simple and effective exercises that will help you improve your overall fitness levels. These simple exercises will help improve strength and cardiovascular fitness.','Perrin Park, Toowong','2017-07-28 21:00:00','2017-07-28 22:00:00','Brisbane City Council','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0),('Boxercise','Bookings essential. Increase your fitness using general boxing techniques, combinations and punches incorporating legs, arms, abs and running into the workout. A great way to get active, increase your cardio fitness and build all-over strength.','Majestic Park, Coorparoo','2017-07-28 21:00:00','2017-07-28 22:00:00','Brisbane City Council','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0),('Yoga','Breath in the fresh air and outdoors while actively participating in a full body workout with yoga sequences, breathing techniques and relaxation. The stretching will benefit cyclists and sports enthusiasts. A full workout to balance the body, heart and mind.  Ferguson Park is