INSERT INTO `Events` VALUES ('Connecting Waves: A Saltwater Woman Living on Desert Country Exhibition','Elisa Jane Carmichael is a Ngughi woman from Quandamooka country living on Arrernte country in Mparntwe (Alice Springs). As the Gilimbaa Artist in Residence, she is recording and documenting her personal and creative journey as a saltwaterwoman living in desert country, weaving and painting her connection to the sand and sea and home country through woven objects and canvases. Gallery is open from 10am-5pm Wednesday to Friday and 9am-3pm on Saturday. This exhibition is a part of the Quandamooka Festival 2017 and Brisbane City Council’s Black History Month.','Onespace Gallery, 13a Gladstone Road, Highgate Hill','2017-07-04 14:00:00','2017-08-05 14:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Exhibition','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Jan Powers Farmers Markets','Every Saturday morning, the walkway at the front of Brisbane Powerhouse fills with market stalls selling a variety of fresh products. Pick up your morning coffee and enjoy the food, fresh produce, meat, seafood, cakes bread and more on offer. You can also bring your dog along to this pooch friendly market.','Brisbane Powerhouse, New Farm','2017-07-28 20:00:00','2017-07-29 02:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Markets','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Yoga','Breath in the fresh air and outdoors while actively participating in a full body workout with yoga sequences, breathing techniques and relaxation. The stretching will benefit cyclists and sports enthusiasts. A full workout to balance the body, heart and mind. Ferguson Park is located behind Bracken Ridge Library.&nbsp;','Ferguson Park, Bracken Ridge','2017-07-28 21:15:00','2017-07-28 22:15:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Pilates','Stretching and strengthening exercises targeted at functional movement and core muscle strengthening. Exercises are designed to improve posture and help reduce risk of injury.','Sherwood Arboretum, Sherwood','2017-07-28 21:30:00','2017-07-28 22:30:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Zumba® fitness','Ditch the workout, join the party with a fun filled dance fitness class to music from all around the world. Options for all ages and fitness levels.','C.B. Mott Park, Holland Park','2017-07-28 21:30:00','2017-07-28 22:30:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Karate and self defence for all','Bookings essential. Karate and self defence for women, men and children. Learn the discipline of self-defence including confidence, goal setting and personal fitness. Participants will be active by stretching, increasing core strength, agility and mobility. Specific Karate movements increase aerobic capacity.','7th Brigade Park, Chermside','2017-07-28 22:00:00','2017-07-28 23:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Outdoor group training','Live longer healthier lifestyles with cutting edge training techniques. Get the most out of a basic but effective education on nutrition.','Svoboda Park, Kuraby','2017-07-28 22:00:00','2017-07-28 23:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Tai Chi Qigong','This dynamic activity is invigorating, works with both your body and your mind and will help you feel relaxed, refreshed and calm. Tai Chi is becoming recognised as the world\'s most beneficial healthy system. Rejuvenate your body and learn to create a tranquil mind. Join any week - all welcome.','New Farm Park, New Farm','2017-07-28 22:00:00','2017-07-28 23:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Yoga on the river','Join us for Hatha yoga classes that are suitable for every body. Move, breath and stretch. All levels catered for.','Captain Burke Park, Kangaroo Point','2017-07-28 22:00:00','2017-07-28 23:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Zumba fitness','Ditch the workout, join the party with a fun filled dance fitness class to music from all around the world. Options for all ages and fitness levels.','Kalinga Park, Kalinga','2017-07-28 22:00:00','2017-07-28 23:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Forest Light - Recent Works By Michael Einersen','A series of oils continuing the artist\'s pursuit of the elusive play of light in Australian forests. The works concentrate mainly on Springbrook and Lamington National Parks and Moggil Conservation Park. A preview of selected works can be viewed at Michael Einersen. Eftpos will be available.&nbsp; Location: Meet at the Richard Randall Art Studio','Brisbane Botanic Gardens Mt Coot-tha','2017-07-28 22:00:00','2017-07-29 07:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Exhibition','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Boxing circuit','Boxing is a great way to improve core and upper body strength. Come along and box your way to fitness.','Lions Park','2017-07-28 22:45:00','2017-07-28 23:30:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Chair yoga','Learn limbering, stretching, strengthening, breathing, relaxation and meditation methods that are designed for people who have difficulty getting up and down from the ground. This is a GOLD event suitable for ages 50 years and over.','Bracken Ridge Hall, Bracken Ridge','2017-07-28 22:45:00','2017-07-28 23:45:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Fitness','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('First 5 Forever children\'s storytime','Experience the magic of storytime with your child at the library. This interactive session includes stories, songs and mark-making activities for children. Ideal for children aged 2-5 years. The First 5 Forever initiative is funded by the Queensland Government.','Bracken Ridge Library','2017-07-28 23:00:00','2017-07-28 23:30:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Family','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Maker space on Saturdays','Drop into the library on Saturdays and get creative with our free craft. Ideal for children aged 4-11 years.','Everton Park Library','2017-07-28 23:00:00','2017-07-29 05:30:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Family','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Southside community craft circle','This craft group makes clothes, rugs and toys to support disadvantaged children in Queensland. New members welcome. Please call Wendy on (07) 3341 2039 or Lois on (07) 3216 7479 for more information.','Coopers Plains Library','2017-07-28 23:00:00','2017-07-29 02:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Family','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('First 5 Forever babies, books and rhymes','Meet other parents and babies for a fun session of singing, clapping and dancing. Learn songs and action rhymes to nurture your baby\'s pre-literacy, communication, language and social skills.&nbsp; Ideal for babies aged up to one year. The First 5 Forever initiative is funded by the Queensland Government.','Kenmore Library','2017-07-28 23:30:00','2017-07-29 00:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Family','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('First 5 Forever children\'s storytime','Experience the magic of storytime with your child at the library. This interactive session includes stories, songs and mark making activities for young children. Ideal for children aged 2-5 years. The First Five Forever initiative is funded by the Queensland Government.','Wynnum Library','2017-07-28 23:30:00','2017-07-29 00:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Family','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/'),('Multicultural Festival','Join us at South East Queensland\'s largest annual community and cultural event at the Gold Coast Multicultural Festival, and experience a full day of fun for the whole family. With international acts from up to 35 nations across three festival stages, as well as sixty-five stalls of international food, art and crafts, and information on particular cultures, you will be able to experience the whole world in one day!','Southport Broadwater Parklands ','2017-08-06 10:00:00','2017-08-06 16:00:00','Gold Coast','Featured Events','Www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au',0,'Exhibition','www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au/'),('Children\'s cycling course','Progression from Training Wheels. Get your little one onto two wheels while learning tips to continue the fun at home. Children must be accompanied by an adult for this course.','Pedal Park Aura','2017-09-21 10:00:00','2017-09-21 11:30:00','Sunshine Coast','General Events','www.sunshinecoast.qld.gov.au',0,'Family','https://www.sunshinecoast.qld.gov.au/'),('Buderim Street Party','Big annual event held first Saturday night in August, where greater Buderim comes alive to party as a community. The main thoroughfare through Buderim Village is blocked off and joins the myriad carparks and public spaces, as stages for a wide variety of food stalls, musicians, dancers and performers. This is a great family night, but has something for everyone in the Buderim and nearby Communities.','Burnett and Main Streets Buderim','2017-08-05 17:30:00','2017-08-05 22:30:00','Sunshine Coast','General Events','www.buderim.com/buderim-street-party',0,'Exhibition','https://www.sunshinecoast.qld.gov.au/'),('Retro Fantastic','As part of the Festival of Community Halls in August, Mapleton Hall will host a 1960\'s day featuring themed activities, music, food and historical displays.','Mapleton Hall, 31 Obi Obi Rd, Mapleton','2017-08-05 09:00:00','2017-08-05 17:00:00','Sunshine Coast','General Events','www.sunshinecoast.qld.gov.au',0,'Exhibition','https://www.sunshinecoast.qld.gov.au/Experience-Sunshine-Coast/Events/Whats-On/3358'),('Annual Orchid Show','Annual Orchid Show','Millwell Road Community Centre,11 Millwell Road East, Maroochydore,','2017-08-04 08:00:00','2017-08-05 14:00:00','Sunshine Coast','General Events','www.sunshinecoast.qld.gov.au',0,'Exhibition','https://www.sunshinecoast.qld.gov.au/Experience-Sunshine-Coast/Events/Whats-On/3371'),('50th Anniversary Event: Our Sunshine Coast Concert','Our Sunshine Coast Concert is a community concert in celebration of the 50th Anniversary of Naming of the Sunshine Coast. This community event draws together local artists and community groups to create an outstanding event and musical experience to commemorate this historic occasion. \n','Sunshine Coast Stadium, 31 Sportsmans Parade Bokarina','2017-08-06 14:00:00','2017-08-06 16:00:00','Sunshine Coast','Major Event','www.sunshinecoast.qld.gov.au',0,'Exhibition','https://www.sunshinecoast.qld.gov.au/Experience-Sunshine-Coast/Events/Whats-On/3241'),('Transform your life with meditation','Are you struggling to make meditation a healthy habit? What if we could assist you in fast tracking your practice by helping \nyou implement a tailor-made meditation program – one that you actually \nenjoyed and looked forward to each day?','Australian School of Meditation and Yoga','2017-08-10 19:00:00','2017-08-10 21:30:00','Gold Coast','General Events','Www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au',0,'Fitness','http://www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au/transform-your-life-with-meditation-41651.html'),('Live at the Lake','An eclectic mix of ingredients blended to create a dazzling ensemble of sparkle, aroma, music, dance, shopping, designed to delight the senses!','Lake Orr, Central Varsity Lakes','2017-08-03 15:00:00','2017-08-03 18:00:00','Gold Coast','General Events','Www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au',0,'Markets','http://www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au/live-at-the-lake-41385.html'),('Big Fit Day Out','Winterfest\'s final event is an action-packed morning of all things fitness.','Lake Orr, Central Varsity Lakes','2017-08-06 07:00:00','2017-08-06 16:00:00','Gold Coast','General Events','Www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au',0,'Fitness','http://www.goldcoast.qld.gov.au/big-fit-day-out-41384.html'),('By the river with jazz and food trucks','Bring a picnic blanket, friends and your furry friends to enjoy a lazy Sunday on the banks of the Brisbane River with music and food trucks.','Newstead Park, 199 Breakfast Creek Road, Newstead','2017-08-06 11:00:00','2017-08-06 16:00:00','Brisbane','General Events','https://www.data.brisbane.qld.gov.au/data/dataset/brisbane-city-council-events',0,'Family','https://www.brisbane.qld.gov.au/whats-on/event/river-jazz-food-trucks'),('The Bodyguard -The Musical','Former Secret Service agent turned bodyguard, Frank Farmer, is hired to protect superstar Rachel Marron from an unknown stalker. Each expects to be in charge – what they don’t expect is